In the field of mathematics, the '''Goss zeta function,''' named after [[David Goss]], is an analogue of the [[Riemann zeta function]] for [[function field of an algebraic variety|function fields]]. {{harvtxt|Sheats|1998}} proved that it satisfies an analogue of the [[Riemann hypothesis]].

